description:
No other food can bring comfort and satisfaction like a delicious bowl of Udon. In order to offer you a deep and solid flavor, we've combined a delicate Japanese style broth with cooked Udon noodles and then added shiitake mushrooms, bok choy, and tofu.

Directions:

Microwave:
1. Place noodles, soup base and dry topping in bowl. Add water up to the line. 2. Place the lid loosely and microwave on high for 2 minutes. (Caution! Bowl will be hot) 3. Stir well before serving. Enjoy! Based on 1200 watt microwave. Microwave oven power may vary; adjust cook time to individual microwave oven.

Alternative cooking method:
Place dry topping mix, noodle and soup base in the bowl. Add boiling water up to the line. Cover with lid and let stand for 2 minutes until noodles are tender, stir well and serve. Enjoy! Try These Serving Tips: Mix in sliced shiitake mushrooms. Top with fried tofu or fish cake. Add cooked chicken or shrimp for a more satisfying meal. Store in a cool dry place. Avoid direct sunlight.

description:
Discover the world of Asian flavors with Simply Asia Rice Noodles Soup Bowl. Our soup bowl combines noodles with delicious broth, vegetables and traditional seasoning for a quick and satisfying meal.

Directions
Microwaving:
Carefully peel back lid to open bowl halfway. Remove seasoning, vegetable and oil packets from bowl. Empty contents of packets into bowl. Microwave: 1. Pour 1-1/2 cups water into bowl, filling bowl to the lower top ridge. Cover with lid. 2. Microwave on high 2 to 3 minutes or until water is hot. 3. Let stand 1 to 2 minuets or until noodles soften. Remove lid; stir well. Enjoy! Microwave ovens vary; cooking times may need to be adjusted. Caution: Bowl and contents will be hot. Handle with care to avoid spilling or burning yourself.

Boiling Water:
1. Pour 1-1/2 cups boiling water into bowl, filling bowl to the lower top ridge. Cover with lid. 2. Let stand 3 to 4 minutes or until noodles soften. Remove lid; stir well. Enjoy!
